**Migrated view (line 136):**
```javascript
onPress={handleContinue}
```

The original passes `{ pointsSelected, reaisSelected }` as an argument, but the migrated version passes nothing. Let me check what the index.tsx handleContinue does:

In the migrated index.tsx (line 89-107), handleContinue doesn't accept any parameters - it calculates the values itself:
```javascript
const handleContinue = () => {
  // ...
  const reaisValue = conversionFactor * getParsePoints(pointsValue);
  navigation.navigate('InvoiceCashbackSummary', {
    pointsSelected: getParsePoints(pointsValue),
    reaisSelected: reaisValue,
    // ...
  });
};
```

While in the original index.tsx (line 72-90), handleContinue ALSO doesn't accept parameters. Wait, that means the original VIEW was passing parameters that the INDEX function doesn't use! So this is actually a BUG FIX - the migrated code removed the redundant parameter passing.

Also notice `direction="row"` in original changed to `direction` (boolean) in migrated - this might be a prop API change.

